Package smarthome.domain.reading

Class Reading

java.lang.Object
smarthome.domain.reading.Reading
All Implemented Interfaces:
AggregateRoot<ReadingId>, DomainEntity<ReadingId>
public class Reading extends Object implements AggregateRoot<ReadingId>
The Reading class represents a reading from a sensor in a smart home system. Each reading has a unique ID, a reading value, a sensor ID, and a timestamp.

    • Reading

      protected Reading (ReadingId readingId, Value value, SensorId sensorId, TimeStamp timeStamp)
      Constructs a new Reading with the given reading ID, value, sensor ID, and timestamp. If the reading ID is null, a new one is automatically generated. If the value, sensor ID, or timestamp is null, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
      Parameters:
      readingId - the unique ID of the reading. If null, a new ID is generated.
      value - the value of the reading. Must not be null.
      sensorId - the ID of the sensor that produced the reading. Must not be null.
      timeStamp - the timestamp of when the reading was taken. Must not be null.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if value, sensorId, or timeStamp is null.
